		on Sunday April 21, 2024 @08:01AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23297300&amp;cid=64411784">#64411784</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64411784"><p>When I was supporting 911 call centres, there were always multiple call centres using each other for fail over.</p><p>A covered region would have a primary and backup call centre, and another region would temporarily take the calls during a migration between the two.</p><p>In terms of interruption of service... there was none.  Though every time we did the fail over testing I was always stressed the switch wouldn't work.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64411784">
